The paper discusses the real-time performance of spectrum management infrastructure in Cognitive Radio Networks, which involves network communication and database management. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT), cognitive radio (cs.CR), distributed computing (cs.DC), and control systems (cs.SY) in its analysis and modeling.
